Malaysian police have arrested three Maldivian students in Malaysia for allegedly possessing narcotics. A foreign ministry official said that they were arrested on Thursday night. The official also said that they were arrested at a show in the Cheras suburban area of Kuala Lampur, Malaysia.  But the official declined to disclose the reason for arrest. Six people have died due to drug overdose on Friday night at a music show held in Bukit Jalil Stadium. The Malaysia-based Star Online has quoted Malaysian police saying that they had arrested 22 people - three of them are foreigners - from the Future Music Festival Asia 2014 show, for possession of narcotics. The foreign ministry official said that the arrested students are under police custody and that the ministry is observing their status closely.  The ministry did not give any further detail. 